//! Plan 15-02 Wave-0 — HDBSCAN (HDBS-01..04) oracle gate suite.
//!
//! This REPLACES the Phase-12 shell convention tests with the full Nyquist gate
//! suite each later HDBSCAN wave turns green. Every gate loads a committed
//! `hdbscan_*.npz` oracle fixture (generated by `scripts/gen_oracle.py` against
//! `sklearn.cluster.HDBSCAN` 1.9.0 + `hdbscan` 0.8.44 — see that file for the
//! design rationale; no Python at test time) and asserts the fitted estimator vs
//! the oracle:
//!
//!   - `labels_match_sklearn` — per metric × {f32,f64}, fitted `labels_` is a
//!     `-1`-PINNED permutation of sklearn's (`best_match_accuracy_pinned_noise
//!     == 1.0`, HDBS-02 / D-03).
//!   - `tie_break_exact` — the tie-heavy + duplicate-point fixture (D-04 TRUE
//!     GATE): same pinned-noise gate over an adversarial tie-heavy MST design,
//!     and the duplicate row (R-9) must share its partner's label.
//!   - `probabilities_match` — per-point `probabilities_` vs sklearn ≤1e-5
//!     (HDBS-01 / D-06).
//!   - `outlier_scores_match` — per-point GLOSH `outlier_scores_` vs hdbscan
//!     0.8.44 ≤1e-5 (HDBS-03 / D-07).
//!   - `centers_match` — `centroids_`/`medoids_` vs sklearn ≤1e-5 under the SAME
//!     label permutation (HDBS-04 / Pitfall 6).
//!   - `selection_knobs` — the nested-density fixture's non-default eom/leaf/
//!     epsilon/max_cluster_size/alpha label vectors are each an exact pinned-noise
//!     permutation of the corresponding oracle (HDBS-01 / D-09).
//!   - `build_validation` — `min_cluster_size`/`min_samples`/`max_cluster_size`/
//!     `alpha`/minkowski-`p` are rejected at build (data-independent, D-08).
//!   - `memory_gate` — re-construct + re-fit does not grow `live_bytes`, and the
//!     device front-end keeps `peak_bytes` sub-quadratic (no `n×n` resident).
//!   - `edge_cases` — all-noise / single-cluster / n<min_cluster_size match
//!     sklearn.
//!
//! WAVE-0 STATUS: the back-end algorithm is NOT built yet — the shell `fit` is
//! still trivial and the extended `Metric`, score/center accessors, and
//! non-Euclidean metrics do not exist. Gates that depend on those symbols are
//! `#[ignore]`d with a `// un-ignore in 15-NN` marker; their bodies are written
//! to COMPILE against the current shell (they load the fixture and exercise the
//! pinned-noise matcher / `assert_close` helper on the oracle arrays as a
//! self-consistency placeholder) so the file compiles green in Wave 0. The later
//! waves replace each placeholder body with the real fit-vs-oracle comparison and
//! drop the `#[ignore]`. `build_validation` runs NOW (the build path exists).
//!
//! f64 cases carry the `skip_f64_with_log` capability gate verbatim (cpu runs
//! f64; rocm skips per the CubeCL-HIP F64 gap). Per AGENTS.md §2 tests live in
//! `crates/mlrs-algos/tests/`, never an in-source `#[cfg(test)] mod tests`.

